            <title>[HIVE-23780] Fail dropTable if acid cleanup fails</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-23780</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Acid cleanup happens after dropTable is committed. If cleanup fails for some reason, there are leftover entries in acid tables. This later causes dropped table&apos;s name to be unusable by new tables.&lt;/p&gt;

